    <item>
      <title>Metal nanosheet gas sensors</title>
      <link>https://tarokato3.github.io/post/integrated_metal_nanosheet_gas_sensor/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Dec 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://tarokato3.github.io/post/integrated_metal_nanosheet_gas_sensor/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is known that resistance in nanostructured metals (such as metal nanosheets) changes when molecules chemisorb. By utilizing that phenomena, our research group has been developing &amp;ldquo;Metal nanosheet gas sensors&amp;rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;
Metal nanosheets have many advantages for sensor application over other materials such as metal semiconductor oxides and polymers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sensor size is small &lt;strong&gt;(&amp;lt; 0.01 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;, so easy to integrate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduction of power consumption is possible &lt;strong&gt;(&amp;lt; 0.1 mW)&lt;/strong&gt; by utilizing self-heating effect &lt;a href=&#34;https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/8887245&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;(see this paper as an example)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly sensitive because of the catalysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly stable if choose noble metals as materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have already realized the multimolecule detection of hydrogen (H&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;) and ammonia (NH&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;) by integration of Pt and PtRh nanosheet sensors with a power consumption of less than 1 mW &lt;a href=&#34;https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/8887245&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;(See ref)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img src=&#34;./test.png&#34; alt=&#34;Example image&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The goal of this research is that we realize metal nanosheets sensor systems which can accurately measure  five or more types of low molecules in air or in breath.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
